1
00:00:04,489 --> 00:00:06,575
Papa, what's wrong?

2
00:00:06,656 --> 00:00:08,050
Oh, I'm sorry.

3
00:00:09,589 --> 00:00:14,269
Taro, remember we talked
about Haruta's mom having a baby?

4
00:00:15,330 --> 00:00:16,645
Nope, we didn't.

5
00:00:16,669 --> 00:00:17,871
Yeah, we did.

6
00:00:18,724 --> 00:00:23,623
Taro, would you be happy
with a sibling? A brother or a sister?

7
00:00:24,010 --> 00:00:26,790
Hmm, I dunno.

8
00:00:26,830 --> 00:00:29,950
It'd be fun. Like having a friend.

9
00:00:29,990 --> 00:00:32,118
Hmm, I dunno. Don't want one.

10
00:00:32,317 --> 00:00:33,532
You don't?

11
00:00:34,699 --> 00:00:37,925
Anyway, if you're not reading to me,
can I read manga?

12
00:00:39,990 --> 00:00:41,910
Or check the Doburock fan club.

13
00:00:41,950 --> 00:00:44,237
No, you can't. It's bedtime.

14
00:00:45,438 --> 00:00:46,749
Sorry, sorry.

15
00:00:47,110 --> 00:00:51,636
"'Who are you?'
The lion yelled at my father."

16
00:00:51,910 --> 00:00:55,650
"'My name is Elmer Elevator.'"

17
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:08,123
What are you watching?

18
00:01:08,780 --> 00:01:10,843
A TV show. Obviously.

19
00:01:11,009 --> 00:01:12,255
What kind?

20
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:14,660
Does it matter?

21
00:01:15,620 --> 00:01:18,703
Wait, why are you here?
I can't relax with you around.

22
00:01:19,070 --> 00:01:23,470
Well, I had something to talk about.

23
00:01:23,813 --> 00:01:25,032
Well, I don't.

24
00:01:28,949 --> 00:01:30,690
Oh, oh, right.

25
00:01:32,482 --> 00:01:35,222
Miharu's expecting her second child.

26
00:01:36,326 --> 00:01:38,546
Oh really? Good for her. When's she due?

27
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:43,000
Not sure, but she said
she's in the stable stage now.

28
00:01:43,236 --> 00:01:45,003
She wouldn't have told you otherwise.

29
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:50,550
So this Sunday, my parents are
going to Miharu's place.

30
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:54,311
And they're asking if we wanna come, too.

31
00:01:54,837 --> 00:01:56,196
Ugh, seriously?!

32
00:01:57,760 --> 00:02:02,673
Your parents really drain me.
Especially your mother.

33
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:04,969
I'll think about it.

34
00:02:05,009 --> 00:02:09,693
I get it, but we haven't seen them in ages.
With Covid-19 and all.

35
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:15,320
Oh please. Covid-19 or not, you haven't seen
my parents in five or six years.

36
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:22,170
Well, yeah, but...
Your dad's kinda passive-aggressive.

37
00:02:22,180 --> 00:02:27,196
Ha, look who's talking.
He's nothing compared to your mother.

38
00:02:28,071 --> 00:02:31,520
When it comes to my mom,
her very presence is like a comedy skit.

39
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:35,663
No, she's not funny at all,
even if she was trying to joke.

40
00:02:36,116 --> 00:02:41,326
What's with her constant bragging
about you? I'd rather get snide remarks.

41
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,680
I said I'd think about it, okay?

42
00:02:44,606 --> 00:02:46,846
Dad probably wants to drink
with me too, y'know.

43
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:49,420
See? I'm the one being considerate here.

44
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:53,860
You deserve a snide remark or two, honestly.

45
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:56,646
Well, my dad is
pretty passive-aggressive, though.

46
00:02:57,007 --> 00:02:58,213
Right?

47
00:02:58,773 --> 00:03:00,093
Don't "Right?" me.

48
00:03:01,605 --> 00:03:04,338
Oh, more importantly, you had
a meeting today, right?

49
00:03:04,644 --> 00:03:07,380
You didn't freak out again saying
you can't follow the medical stuff?

50
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:10,760
No, it was totally fine. Besides,

51
00:03:11,034 --> 00:03:13,624
it's just a reenactment show.

52
00:03:13,664 --> 00:03:17,200
Nobody's gonna complain
even if I phone it in.

53
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,880
What kind of attitude is that? Pathetic.

54
00:03:20,220 --> 00:03:22,622
You're seriously so lame when you do that.

55
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,789
What about Nishimura? The previous director.

56
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:28,543
Didn't you cut corners
when working with him last time?

57
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:31,827
Seriously, don't dump
your work on me this time.

58
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:34,450
I won't. I'm totally fine.

59
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:38,136
Besides, that director...

60
00:03:38,382 --> 00:03:42,844
Reenactment shows are all he's got,
so he has no choice but to try hard.

61
00:03:43,343 --> 00:03:49,383
Well, he's handling this project too,
and today he said you're really talented.

62
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:53,290
Obviously. I'm an amateur,
and I still wrote all that.

63
00:03:53,606 --> 00:03:57,826
Meanwhile, you can't write properly even
for these reenactment shows. Pathetic.

64
00:03:57,866 --> 00:04:01,001
Just stop talking.
You disappoint me more every second.

65
00:04:01,041 --> 00:04:07,303
Hey, you were the one asking! Besides,
I was about to start working. See?

66
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:10,020
Right, let's get to work.

67
00:04:13,263 --> 00:04:14,463
Why are you laughing?

68
00:04:14,790 --> 00:04:17,083
Because you're so dumb.

69
00:04:17,383 --> 00:04:19,243
They say dumb guys are cuter, though.

70
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:22,337
You ain't cute. Get to work already, loser.

71
00:04:23,122 --> 00:04:25,122
Yes, yes.

72
00:04:35,696 --> 00:04:41,957
Bacteria attach to the heart wall
and cause infection. Cultured bacteria.

73
00:04:42,330 --> 00:04:44,870
I have no idea what the doctor is saying,

74
00:04:45,056 --> 00:04:50,759
but if I look like I'm working hard,
Chika will definitely help me out.

75
00:04:51,272 --> 00:04:53,412
That smile just now was proof enough.

76
00:04:55,129 --> 00:05:00,630
So does that mean anyone can get it,
regardless of lifestyle?

77
00:05:00,896 --> 00:05:05,810
Well, dialysis patients and diabetics
with weakened immunity are more at risk.

78
00:05:10,528 --> 00:05:12,315
Alright!

79
00:05:15,388 --> 00:05:16,608
Ta-da!

80
00:05:17,301 --> 00:05:18,761
Yay!

81
00:05:19,055 --> 00:05:20,468
Thank you!

82
00:05:23,426 --> 00:05:24,721
Here we go!

83
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:35,373
- Shall we have some action tonight?
- I'm so glad to be alive!

84
00:06:02,024 --> 00:06:04,911
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife

85
00:06:05,617 --> 00:06:06,657
Amazing, right?

86
00:06:06,697 --> 00:06:07,777
Episode 4: Sibling Strategy

87
00:06:07,817 --> 00:06:09,814
After school today, tomorrow's a day off.

88
00:06:09,988 --> 00:06:12,137
So, on Sunday, we can go to Haruta's place.

89
00:06:12,177 --> 00:06:14,297
Grandma and Grandpa
from Tottori are coming, too.

90
00:06:14,337 --> 00:06:16,030
Oh, so you're coming too, Chika?

91
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:19,639
I have to go. Your mom's a pain
if I don't show up.

92
00:06:19,910 --> 00:06:22,902
Great news, Taro. Mommy's coming, too!

93
00:06:23,142 --> 00:06:25,563
All right, do your best at school today!

94
00:06:27,695 --> 00:06:31,739
I know, I know. Do your best!
Mama loves you very much.

95
00:06:32,863 --> 00:06:34,087
Have a good day!

96
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:36,027
Okay, let's go!

97
00:06:37,403 --> 00:06:38,609
Have a good day!

98
00:06:51,573 --> 00:06:53,103
I'm fine from here.

99
00:06:54,223 --> 00:06:55,800
You sure?

100
00:06:56,479 --> 00:06:58,251
- I'll walk with you.
- I said I'm fine.

101
00:07:25,456 --> 00:07:26,796
He went by himself.

102
00:07:27,250 --> 00:07:29,068
Said I don't need to walk him to school.

103
00:07:29,108 --> 00:07:32,150
He's embarrassed to be seen with you.
He's getting pretty independent.

104
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:34,256
- Well, I'm off.
- Okay.

105
00:07:36,215 --> 00:07:38,735
Hey, you'd better actually do some work.

106
00:07:38,775 --> 00:07:42,484
I will. Obviously.
I've got a meeting after this.

107
00:07:43,075 --> 00:07:44,281
And...

108
00:07:46,470 --> 00:07:47,676
How about a kiss?

109
00:07:49,237 --> 00:07:50,451
Not happening.

110
00:08:05,303 --> 00:08:07,530
Taro's off to school.

111
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:12,500
So, I can finally kick back
and watch DVDs and porn.

112
00:08:34,533 --> 00:08:36,657
I know we talked about a cavity,

113
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:39,360
but should we just make it a regular injury?

114
00:08:40,229 --> 00:08:42,360
A cavity's hard to explain,

115
00:08:42,464 --> 00:08:45,240
so we'll say bacteria got in through
a wound somewhere.

116
00:08:47,959 --> 00:08:49,424
You following me?

117
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:52,530
Huh? What?

118
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:57,180
The cause of the protagonist's illness.

119
00:08:58,717 --> 00:09:00,397
Oh, right.

120
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:02,425
I see.

121
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,142
Isn't it almost your wife's turn to step in?

122
00:09:05,215 --> 00:09:07,540
Oh, we got an email from your wife.

123
00:09:07,639 --> 00:09:09,959
She wrote, "Please take care of my husband."

124
00:09:10,152 --> 00:09:14,046
- Huh?
- She wrote, "Please whip him into shape."

125
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:16,206
She's really a great wife, isn't she?

126
00:09:16,666 --> 00:09:19,275
"Worst case, I'll write it again myself."

127
00:09:19,993 --> 00:09:21,733
Could you ask her soon?

128
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:23,546
Yeah, why not? Let's ask her to do it.

129
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:27,053
No, that won't work. She's just an amateur.

130
00:09:27,306 --> 00:09:29,153
Amateurs are what we want.

131
00:09:29,820 --> 00:09:31,435
In any profession.

132
00:09:36,339 --> 00:09:39,092
Taro, you don't wanna bring your manga?

133
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:40,380
But...

134
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:43,698
Hey, put the iPad down.
You can bring it, okay?

135
00:09:43,881 --> 00:09:45,685
Come on. Stop it.

136
00:09:45,725 --> 00:09:51,550
- Hey, don't take it! Give it back!
- Come on, we need to go already.

137
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:55,164
I said you can bring it. Now get ready.

138
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:09,540
Taro, don't read while you're walking.

139
00:10:11,056 --> 00:10:13,623
Fine, can I play
the Switch at Haruta's place?

140
00:10:13,663 --> 00:10:15,223
Sure, if they let you.

141
00:10:15,799 --> 00:10:16,846
Can we buy one?

142
00:10:16,886 --> 00:10:19,119
No, maybe when you're in middle school.

143
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:22,588
I told you before.
When you're in middle school.

144
00:10:28,643 --> 00:10:29,856
Taro!

145
00:10:31,163 --> 00:10:32,623
How are you?

146
00:10:33,096 --> 00:10:36,296
High five! Yay, yay!

147
00:10:37,486 --> 00:10:40,005
Let Grandpa play with you, too.

148
00:10:40,045 --> 00:10:41,873
Stop with the Tottori dialect.

149
00:10:44,819 --> 00:10:49,953
Well, look at you!
You can make stewed dishes like this now?

150
00:10:49,993 --> 00:10:54,836
I mean, I've been making stuff
like this since Taro was born. Right, Chika?

151
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:59,970
Look at this, Papa. You couldn't make this
if your life depended on it.

152
00:11:00,128 --> 00:11:04,143
Lucky you, Taro.
Getting to eat like this every day!

153
00:11:04,183 --> 00:11:07,008
Mom, that's coming off as a dig at Chika.

154
00:11:07,172 --> 00:11:08,732
You're adding fuel to the fire.

155
00:11:09,245 --> 00:11:11,684
Oh, thanks. Wanna have your drink there?

156
00:11:11,724 --> 00:11:13,170
Yeah, thanks.

157
00:11:13,210 --> 00:11:14,690
Mom's just clueless like that.

158
00:11:14,729 --> 00:11:16,470
Nothing wrong with that. It's charming.

159
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:18,860
Wow, this is unnecessarily good.

160
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,860
"Unnecessarily" is uncalled for.

161
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:24,887
If he can cook this well, it's fine
if he's a househusband for now.

162
00:11:24,927 --> 00:11:27,942
Work will come, right, Chika?

163
00:11:28,179 --> 00:11:29,890
Who knows?

164
00:11:29,930 --> 00:11:32,346
Can we not do this right now?

165
00:11:32,590 --> 00:11:35,310
Why don't you two have another kid, too?

166
00:11:36,010 --> 00:11:37,707
Where'd that come from?

167
00:11:37,747 --> 00:11:39,910
Still dropping bombs as always.

168
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:44,110
What bombs? What do you think, Chika?
You'd be fine, right?

169
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:47,500
No, that's absolutely not happening for us.

170
00:11:47,730 --> 00:11:50,479
Oh, don't say that. Even with Taro,

171
00:11:50,519 --> 00:11:54,072
you said you weren't ready,
but it all worked out, didn't it?

172
00:11:54,252 --> 00:11:57,722
Having siblings is better
for Taro, too. Right, Papa?

173
00:11:58,170 --> 00:12:02,290
Enough already. Drop it. It's their business.

174
00:12:02,420 --> 00:12:05,663
But Gota does so much around the house.

175
00:12:06,299 --> 00:12:10,057
You never lifted a finger
with the kids. Always just the work.

176
00:12:10,210 --> 00:12:12,050
Times were different.

177
00:12:12,457 --> 00:12:14,363
Times have nothing to do with it.

178
00:12:14,783 --> 00:12:20,163
I made everything from scratch.
Baby food, all of it.

179
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:24,510
That's why he turned into such a foodie
despite being broke.

180
00:12:25,183 --> 00:12:26,423
A broke foodie.

181
00:12:27,676 --> 00:12:29,196
But isn't that nice, Chika?

182
00:12:29,524 --> 00:12:32,123
He's poor, but doesn't make you feel
like he's that.

183
00:12:32,163 --> 00:12:33,792
Oh, I feel it plenty.

184
00:12:34,778 --> 00:12:37,690
Can we not do this?

185
00:12:37,730 --> 00:12:39,015
Why not?

186
00:12:39,248 --> 00:12:44,936
No matter how much Grandma bullied me,
I never compromised on raising you.

187
00:12:45,010 --> 00:12:46,622
And look how he turned out.

188
00:12:46,762 --> 00:12:50,152
Well, if he were perfect,
that'd be boring, wouldn't it?

189
00:12:50,490 --> 00:12:53,410
Right, Chika? You understand that, don't you?

190
00:12:53,450 --> 00:12:55,417
Who knows?

191
00:12:55,850 --> 00:13:00,296
But Chika, you were the first
to recognize Gota's talent.

192
00:13:00,457 --> 00:13:02,656
You need to nurture it.

193
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,395
Independent films, right?

194
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:09,474
When he said he won some award,
I thought it was just college kid stuff.

195
00:13:09,677 --> 00:13:11,870
Until Chika told me
it was a prestigious award.

196
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:14,596
How long ago was that?
Over twenty years, right?

197
00:13:14,650 --> 00:13:16,590
- Isn't that recent?
- Recent?

198
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:18,700
As always, your family is hilarious.

199
00:13:18,716 --> 00:13:20,776
Not the family. Just Mom.

200
00:13:20,890 --> 00:13:22,203
- Me?
- Yes, you.

201
00:13:22,243 --> 00:13:23,550
Hey!

202
00:13:24,547 --> 00:13:27,700
I met Chika in college, in the film club.

203
00:13:28,091 --> 00:13:31,357
Back then, I'd won an award
for my independent film,

204
00:13:31,503 --> 00:13:35,070
and I was hailed as a rising star
in the amateur film world.

205
00:13:35,830 --> 00:13:40,199
Chika fell for my talent and confessed
her feelings. That's how it started.

206
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:44,410
It wasn't bad, but for Eastwood,
Unforgiven
is still the best one.

207
00:13:44,450 --> 00:13:47,148
- You can't top that.
-
The Bridges of Madison County
is good, too.

208
00:13:47,188 --> 00:13:50,221
- Dude, you're balding.
- Hey, don't say that.

209
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:54,357
My turn, the only Eastwood movie
I know is
Dirty Harry
.

210
00:13:55,190 --> 00:13:58,510
Dirty Harry
, huh. Yeah, that's a solid pick.

211
00:13:59,241 --> 00:14:01,050
But
Tightrope
is amazing too, right?

212
00:14:02,056 --> 00:14:06,342
That's true.
Anything with Eastwood ends up being amazing.

213
00:14:08,089 --> 00:14:10,623
Okay, I'm gonna go sit next to Gota.

214
00:14:11,530 --> 00:14:14,503
Move it. Move, move!

215
00:14:15,290 --> 00:14:18,448
Congratulations on winning the top prize.

216
00:14:18,488 --> 00:14:20,259
I think you're even better than Eastwood.

217
00:14:20,299 --> 00:14:24,317
Thanks. I'm not quite
at his level yet, though.

218
00:14:24,357 --> 00:14:27,330
No, seriously, your film was really amazing.

219
00:14:27,481 --> 00:14:29,161
I seriously respect you.

220
00:14:29,376 --> 00:14:31,082
- You're into that kind of stuff?
- Yes.

221
00:14:31,122 --> 00:14:32,636
What did you like about it?

222
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:36,282
Um, I mean, everything was
just so incredible...

223
00:14:37,283 --> 00:14:38,596
Hey, wanna go out with me?

224
00:14:40,116 --> 00:14:41,116
Huh?

225
00:14:41,152 --> 00:14:44,072
Oh, come on. You totally heard me.

226
00:14:44,129 --> 00:14:46,590
I totally like you, Gota.

227
00:14:46,681 --> 00:14:49,230
You're cute, talented, and just the best.

228
00:14:52,970 --> 00:14:54,176
Thanks.

229
00:14:54,363 --> 00:14:55,869
So cute.

230
00:14:58,290 --> 00:15:04,388
I've been trying to help him grow,
but his weird pride gets in the way.

231
00:15:04,469 --> 00:15:07,321
He's doing a medical reenactment show now,

232
00:15:07,361 --> 00:15:09,420
but he said he couldn't take it seriously.

233
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:12,236
I actually had to write it
for him last time, too.

234
00:15:12,543 --> 00:15:15,070
Having pride isn't a bad thing.

235
00:15:15,157 --> 00:15:16,975
All talented people are like that.

236
00:15:17,361 --> 00:15:18,876
- Is it about a hospital?
- Yeah.

237
00:15:19,063 --> 00:15:23,190
What was it called, dear? That foreign show?

238
00:15:23,230 --> 00:15:25,437
- Foreign show?
- Oh, with the handsome guy in it.

239
00:15:25,676 --> 00:15:29,927
- Handsome guy?
-
AR
! You should write something like that.

240
00:15:30,090 --> 00:15:32,223
That was great, wasn't it, dear?

241
00:15:32,350 --> 00:15:37,474
That's not how it works.
Stop meddling. Let him be an adult.

242
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:43,961
How rude. I let him be one. All I'm saying is
that he does way more than you ever did.

243
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:51,299
What the heck do you mean? Do you know
how busy I was back then?

244
00:15:51,339 --> 00:15:53,750
You could focus entirely on raising the kids.

245
00:15:53,790 --> 00:15:57,050
Okay, okay, let's stop
before this gets out of hand.

246
00:15:57,090 --> 00:15:59,417
Don't embarrass yourselves
in front of your grandkids.

247
00:15:59,638 --> 00:16:02,612
Besides, that show is titled not "AR,"
but
ER
, right?

248
00:16:03,246 --> 00:16:04,530
ER
... So close!

249
00:16:05,759 --> 00:16:08,777
But this all started from the talk
about having a second kid.

250
00:16:08,817 --> 00:16:12,673
Exactly. All I said was maybe
they should have a second child.

251
00:16:12,778 --> 00:16:17,205
Oh, I almost forgot something important.
Granny has cancer.

252
00:16:17,596 --> 00:16:18,890
- What?
- Really?

253
00:16:18,930 --> 00:16:20,410
And a sudden plot twist!

254
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:24,785
That's right, a twist. Right, Papa?
She's got a lump right here.

255
00:16:25,096 --> 00:16:30,598
We don't even know if it's malignant yet.
She still needs a biopsy.

256
00:16:30,796 --> 00:16:33,293
A lump that hard is definitely cancer.

257
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:39,240
So show her one more great-grandchild.
One or two, what's the difference?

258
00:16:40,810 --> 00:16:43,730
We'll figure that out on our own, okay?

259
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:49,241
Besides, even if she does have cancer,
at her age it'd progress slowly.

260
00:16:49,281 --> 00:16:53,826
You don't know that.
It might already be too late.

261
00:16:53,983 --> 00:16:55,508
Enough already, stop!

262
00:16:59,629 --> 00:17:01,210
It always ends up like this.

263
00:17:02,350 --> 00:17:03,950
Chika, I'm sorry about this.

264
00:17:04,283 --> 00:17:06,923
Oh, it's fine. I'm getting used to it.

265
00:17:07,203 --> 00:17:09,063
Yeah, you’ve got to get used to this.

266
00:17:09,103 --> 00:17:10,430
I'd rather not, though.

267
00:17:10,470 --> 00:17:14,731
True, who would?
Now then, let's have a toast! Cheers!

268
00:17:14,771 --> 00:17:15,995
Let's toast!

269
00:17:16,510 --> 00:17:19,565
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

270
00:17:21,957 --> 00:17:23,196
What's this?

271
00:17:23,369 --> 00:17:24,663
I wonder?

272
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:26,370
Delicious.

273
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:28,490
Go on, drink up!

274
00:17:28,530 --> 00:17:30,550
Oh, honestly...

275
00:17:30,976 --> 00:17:32,194
Don't talk, just drink.

276
00:17:39,913 --> 00:17:42,640
Sorry, Miharu.
I'll come pick him up tomorrow.

277
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:44,753
It's totally fine. Haruta is happy, too.

278
00:17:44,966 --> 00:17:47,412
Sorry, it always ends up like this.

279
00:17:47,452 --> 00:17:49,625
Oh, it's fine. I'm getting used to it.

280
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:51,870
Oh, that sounds just like
what you said earlier.

281
00:17:52,076 --> 00:17:53,762
Shall we start round two right here?

282
00:17:53,802 --> 00:17:56,328
No, no, I've already been KO'd.

283
00:17:56,691 --> 00:17:59,044
- Please give our regards to Grandpa.
- I will.

284
00:17:59,175 --> 00:18:00,968
- Well, good night.
- See you.

285
00:18:01,043 --> 00:18:02,283
Be safe.

286
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:05,105
- Good night.
- Thank you.

287
00:18:07,856 --> 00:18:10,696
- You just had to butt in, didn't you?
- No, it was not my fault.

288
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,963
Man, what a tiring day.

289
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,701
I'm the one who's tired here.

290
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:21,547
Just being around your parents wrecks
my mental health.

291
00:18:22,395 --> 00:18:26,140
Wanna grab a quick drink somewhere?
It's been a while without Taro.

292
00:18:26,180 --> 00:18:27,760
Ugh, not with you.

293
00:18:28,429 --> 00:18:31,928
Seriously though, your mom is something else.

294
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:35,873
What about us makes her think
we can afford a second kid?

295
00:18:36,683 --> 00:18:41,390
In this day and age, spouting baseless crap
like "better to have siblings."

296
00:18:41,657 --> 00:18:44,250
And what do you even think
about your own mother?

297
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:45,963
Don't you think she's insane?

298
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:49,805
On top of that, why did I have to sit
through her bragging about you?

299
00:18:49,845 --> 00:18:51,580
My day off was total crap.

300
00:18:51,788 --> 00:18:55,295
Well, my mom is outdated, I'll give you that.

301
00:18:55,481 --> 00:19:02,396
But, you know, a second kid...
It might not be such a bad idea.

302
00:19:02,736 --> 00:19:05,776
Huh? What do you mean by that?

303
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:16,090
I mean, Taro's the way he is,
so maybe having a sibling would help him.

304
00:19:16,510 --> 00:19:20,970
Whoa, hold on. I'm the one
who'd have to take off work and give birth.

305
00:19:21,450 --> 00:19:24,570
And I'm the one raising the kid
and earning the living, too.

306
00:19:24,810 --> 00:19:28,483
Do you get all that before you talk?
And I'm 40, you know.

307
00:19:29,610 --> 00:19:31,623
I know. I've been thinking about it.

308
00:19:31,663 --> 00:19:32,883
Bullshit.

309
00:19:33,090 --> 00:19:34,302
What?

310
00:19:34,570 --> 00:19:39,236
You figure if we're having a second kid,
we'll do it again. That's gross.

311
00:19:40,030 --> 00:19:42,050
What are you saying? That's not it.

312
00:19:42,090 --> 00:19:45,123
Using that as an excuse is
seriously the worst.

313
00:19:48,323 --> 00:19:49,660
Okay, well then...

314
00:19:54,152 --> 00:19:55,472
Then...

315
00:19:57,411 --> 00:19:59,085
Let me do it.

316
00:19:59,972 --> 00:20:04,359
I don't wanna use stuff like this
as an excuse either!

317
00:20:05,703 --> 00:20:10,963
See, you
were
using it as an excuse.
Now I wanna sleep with you even less.

318
00:20:21,804 --> 00:20:24,120
By the way, you emailed Nishimura, right?

319
00:20:24,956 --> 00:20:29,650
Huh? Don't just change
the topic so suddenly, dumbass.

320
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:33,450
It was about the reenactment show.
Why do you pull stuff like that?

321
00:20:34,206 --> 00:20:37,271
Because you barely work,
I have to cover for your sorry ass.

322
00:20:37,311 --> 00:20:41,290
That's not covering for me.
You're just sucking up to him.

323
00:20:41,380 --> 00:20:43,828
Excuse me? Sucking up?
Then do your damn job properly.

324
00:20:43,868 --> 00:20:46,595
I will. It's my job anyway.

325
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:49,492
You blew it last time.

326
00:20:50,618 --> 00:20:53,192
Don't take it out on me
just because we're not doing it.

327
00:20:53,542 --> 00:20:57,332
My day off is ruined, and I got hit
with old-fashioned emotional abuse.

328
00:20:57,372 --> 00:20:59,340
I'm absolutely livid.

329
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:04,790
I'm going out drinking alone.
Don't follow me.

330
00:21:19,792 --> 00:21:21,965
That pig.

331
00:21:33,996 --> 00:21:36,656
Even porn can't calm me down.

332
00:21:37,020 --> 00:21:39,989
Why do I have to put up
with that kind of abuse?

333
00:21:43,810 --> 00:21:46,963
It's your fault. This is straight-up abuse.

334
00:21:50,787 --> 00:21:52,747
Maybe I really should cheat on her.

335
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:07,486
That bastard husband
of mine was cheating. Unforgivable.

336
00:22:14,749 --> 00:22:15,749
Next Episode Preview

337
00:22:15,777 --> 00:22:18,646
- Chika might be cheating, too.
- Huh?

338
00:22:18,686 --> 00:22:20,019
I'm going to see Nishimura.

339
00:22:20,059 --> 00:22:21,212
Wait, what's that about?

340
00:22:21,252 --> 00:22:23,372
It's because you are useless.

341
00:22:23,420 --> 00:22:26,095
It's not confirmed
that Chika's actually cheating, but...

342
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:27,746
Everyone's struggling.

343
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:29,486
Fine.
